    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the `ollama rename` feature. It touches exactly **4 files**, all using existing utilities — no new packages required.\n\n---\n\n## What Will Be Changed\n\n### 1. `api/types.go` — Add `RenameRequest` struct\nInsert after `CopyRequest` (line 765). Identical shape: `Source` + `Destination` fields.\n\n### 2. `api/client.go` — Add `Rename` client method\nInsert after `Copy` (line 387). Posts to `POST /api/rename`, no response body — same pattern as `Copy`.\n\n### 3. `server/routes.go` — Add `RenameHandler` + register route\nInsert after `CopyHandler` (line 1483). The handler:\n- Parses/validates both names using the same `model.ParseName` + `getExistingName` pattern as `CopyHandler`\n- **404**: calls `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` — returns `os.ErrNotExist` if source is absent\n- **409**: calls `manifest.PathForName(dst)` + `os.Stat()` — if the file exists, destination already taken\n- Calls `CopyModel(src, dst)` to create the destination manifest (blobs are always shared, never duplicated)\n- Calls `m.Remove()` to delete the source manifest (deliberately omits `RemoveLayers()` since blobs are still referenced by the destination)\n- Route registered as `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after the copy route (line 1698)\n\n### 4. `cmd/cmd.go` — Add CLI handler + cobra command\n- `RenameHandler` function after `CopyHandler` (line 1350): calls `client.Rename`, prints `\"renamed 'X' to 'Y'\"`\n- `renameCmd` cobra command after `copyCmd` (line 2263): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, same `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- `renameCmd` added to both the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand`",
